Photo by RegenHealth on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Autena @autenaasefirad Yes, normalize therapy. But also make it affordable. Far too many people turn therapy away because one visit costs hundreds of dollars. Mental health care should not be a luxury item.'.

node.text:
Why is it that the things we need the most are often the most expensive—therapy being
one the most common. We have to find a way to create accessible and affordable therapy. Tending to our mental health is as important as it gets, we must make it a priority. Even if “you can’t afford therapy” right now, make sure you create avenues to unpack your thoughts and emotions. Whether it’s a family member, a friend, a significant other, or a pet; find a way to take care of your brain. 🧠🎭
via @mh.advocates @autenaasefirad

Photo by RegenHealth on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'STOP SAYING SORRY FOR C* BEING BUSY SETTING NOT BEING CRYING OR AND OWNING BOUNDARIES PERFECT SHOWING YOUR TIME FOR YOURSELF ALWAYS EMOTIONS SELFCARESPOTLIGHT'.

node.text:
Stop apologizing for being human, we all experience setbacks and this is a normal part of the human experience. I am definitely guilty of this, if I start to cry in front of someone, I’ll immediately apologize- so if you do this, just know you’re not alone!⁣
⁣
Recognizing our patterns of apologizing for things that humanize us is a good first step. Let’s normalize setting boundaries and showing emotions. It’s okay if I’m busy and it’s okay if I’m not perfect- I am me and others must accept that ❤️⁣
⁣
✒️＋🎨 @selfcarespotlight ❤️
